# Belt-and-suspenders for shared Apache/LiteSpeed hosting (e.g. Hostinger).
# The actual fix for the 403 was moving index.html to the repo root — most
# hosts already default DirectoryIndex to index.html — but this makes it
# explicit rather than relying on that default, and disables directory
# listings so /js/ or /css/ can't be browsed directly.
DirectoryIndex index.html

Options -Indexes

<IfModule mod_mime.c>
  AddType application/javascript .js
  AddType text/css .css
</IfModule>
